}{}$\mu =\left(0,0.025,0.05,0.1,0.15,0.2,0.3,0.4\right) $\end{document}. This gave us 40 simulation data sets.
We applied four DMR finding methods (DMRcate, bumphunter, Probe Lasso, comb-p) to the simulation data sets generated in step 3.
Finally, we compared results of these methods on precision, power, AuPR, MCC, F1, type I error rate, size of the DMRs, execution time as well as overlap of DMRs identified by different methods.

The 14 methylation samples were randomly divided into two groups. Differential methylation of a small subset (i.e. 500) of the clusters were simulated by adding a small treatment effect \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
